com.bluegosling.apt.reflect

Class ArDeclaredType

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.bluegosling.apt.reflect.ArType
      • com.bluegosling.apt.reflect.ArDeclaredType
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ArAnnotatedConstruct

    public class ArDeclaredType
extends ArType
    A declared type. In core reflection, this would be represented by a Class or, for annotated types, by an AnnotatedType that does not implement any of that interface's sub-interfaces (e.g. not a parameterized type, array type, type variable, or wildcard type). In some ways, it like ParameterizedType except that it can be used to represent raw and non-generic types, too. Unlike Class, a declared type will not represent an array type or a primitive type.
    See Also:
    ParameterizedType, DeclaredType
